n","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Arden   with prosthetic <i>H-</i>.","English: habitational name, either from Haredene Wood in East Tisbury (Wiltshire), or from Haredon (in Ugborough, Devon). The first placename probably derives from Old English <i>hara</i> ‘hare’ + <i>denu</i> ‘valley’. The second is from Old English <i>hara</i> + <i>dūn</i> ‘hare hill’.","English: variant of   Harding  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Arden","meanings":["English: habitational name, either from the district of Arden in Warwickshire or from Arden in Bredbury (Cheshire). The first placename is thought to be derived from a Celtic word meaning ‘high place’, cognate with <i>Ardennes</i>, the name of a forested region on the borders between northeastern France and eastern Belgium. The second derives from Old English <i>hēah</i> ‘high’ + <i>worthign</i> ‘enclosed settlement’."]},{"name":"Harwin","meanings":["English (Norfolk): of Norman origin, from the Middle English personal name <i>Hard(e)win</i> (Old French <i>Hard(o)uin</i>, composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>hard</i> ‘hardy’, ‘brave’ + <i>win</i> ‘friend’). Compare   Harden   1."]}]},{"name":"Avis","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Norman French form of the ancient Germanic name <i>Aveza</i>, derived from a short form of one or more compound names containing the first element <i>av</i> (as in   Ava ;  the meaning is uncertain). The correspondence in form to the Latin word <i>avis</i> ‘bird’ is coincidental."],"variants":[{"name":"Avice","meanings":["From a Norman French form of the ancient Germanic name <i>Aveza</i>, derived from a short form of one or more compound names containing the first element <i>av</i> (as in   Ava ;  the meaning is uncertain). The correspondence in form to the Latin word <i>avis</i> ‘bird’ is coincidental."]}]},{"name":"Anna","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["variant of   Anne  , in common use as a given name in most European languages. Among people with a classical education, it has from time to time been associated with  Virgil's  Aeneid, where it is borne by the sister of  Dido , Queen of Carthage. This Phoenician name may ultimately be of Semitic origin, and thus related to the biblical <i>Anne</i>. However, the connection, if it exists, is indirect rather than direct."],"variants":[{"name":"Anne","meanings":["Pet form of   Ann   or   Anne ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Avis Anna Harden was born in 1340, in Castley, Yorkshire, England, her father, Nicholas Harden, was 19 and her mother, Margaret Blanche Alddersley, was 13. She married Sir John Marshall Earl of Pembroke. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 1 daughter. She died in 1370, in Hingham, Norfolk, England, at the age of 30."},"et":{"1340–1370":"1340–1370","1358–1438":"1358–1438","1364–Female":"1364–Surnud","1370–1432":"1370–1432","1400–1437":"1400–1437","1321–1418":"1321–1418","1327–1418":"1327–1418","1327":"1327","1437":"1437","1358":"1358","1400":"1400","1432":"1432","1321":"1321","1364":"1364","1340":"1340","1370":"1370","1418":"1418","1438":"1438","Norbury, Derbyshire, England":"Norbury, Derbyshire, England","Hingham, Norfolk, England":"Hingham, Norfolk, England","Beverly,  Yorkshire,  ,  England":"Beverly, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Castley, Yorkshire, England":"Castley, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1340–1370":"1340–1370","1358–1438":"1358–1438","1364–Female":"1364–Kuollut","1370–1432":"1370–1432","1400–1437":"1400–1437","1321–1418":"1321–1418","1327–1418":"1327–1418","1327":"1327","1437":"1437","1358":"1358","1400":"1400","1432":"1432","1321":"1321","1364":"1364","1340":"1340","1370":"1370","1418":"1418","1438":"1438","Norbury, Derbyshire, England":"Norbury, Derbyshire, England","Hingham, Norfolk, England